/*

Despite being an incredibly popular demo video, there is no code golf for Bad Apple yet!

The Challenge:

Output one frame of your choice from anywhere in the video, in ascii, or any other method of graphical output (such as pygame, turtle, LED lights, GCODE that 3d prints a frame, anything goes).

The Rules:

Standard rules on loopholes apply

The frame must not be a singular solid colour (or 99%, don't try cheating this by picking a frame with a single pixel of white in a corner or something)

A frame is "too boring" if it shows no object or character in main focus

Resolution of the frame must be (at minimum) 10*10. Any downsampling can be used

Scoring is done based on standard Code Golf rules

An example ascii output is available at this link (Note that it is animated, but you only need a single frame)
https://joeheyming.github.io/badapple/

Good luck!

*/

